title: Z.ai native Anthropic-compatible provider path missing
---
cx-reviewer audit (2026-05-21): src/provider.ml has zai/zai_coding default base URLs but no Anthropic-compatible native provider. There is no src/provider_zai.ml and no Zai kind in provider.ml::detect_kind. Z.ai/GLM requests route through OpenAI-compatible /chat/completions at provider.ml:941, not the official anthropic-compat /anthropic/v1/messages endpoint.

Impact:
- Tool serialization for GLM/Z.ai goes via OpenAI format (probably works since Z.ai accepts it).
- But the bigger anthropic-compat surface (tool_use blocks, content blocks, etc.) is not exercised.
- Likely fine for now; flag as architectural cleanup.

Fix:
- Create src/provider_zai.ml mirroring provider_minimax.ml with anthropic-compat endpoint, tools_to_anthropic_json, and message conversion.
- Register native_complete for ZaiCoding/Zai kinds in provider_init.ml.
- Or document explicitly that Z.ai uses OpenAI-compat path and remove the implication it's anthropic-compat in docs.

Tag: zai, provider, architecture